      Submitted by Carolcar on Fri, 25/10/2024 - 05:46
      Permalink
        May I know if the second verb 'will'(will realize) can be omitted in this sentence ?
        "I hope that people will spend more time on this and that they will realize the importance of it."
      - Log in or register to post comments
        Submitted by Peter M. on Fri, 25/10/2024 - 06:23
        In reply to by
        Permalink
          Hello Carolcar,
          No, you can't omit 'realize' here. We omit some elements of a sentence when they are repeated or obvious from the sentence structure, so here you could omit 'that' (repeated), 'they' (referring to 'people'), and 'will' (repeated). This gives you this sentence:
            I hope that people will spend more time on this and realize the importance of it.
          Peter
          The LearnEnglish Team
